For this problem, we will use the relationship between the equity beta as well as the asset beta which was solved in the previous problem. The formula that relates this two is given as:

$$\begin{aligned}
\beta_E&=\beta_A\times\left(1+\dfrac{\text{D}}{\text{E}}\right)
\end{aligned}$$

Where,

$$\begin{aligned}
\beta_E&=\text{Equity beta}\\
\beta_A&=\text{Asset beta}\\
\dfrac{\text{D}}{\text{E}}&=\text{Debt-equity ratio}
\end{aligned}$$
